Writes the current value of the variable to the trace output For each integral type there exists a method

template<InternalTracer::TraceMask mask>
template<class T>
void _FunctionTracer< mask >::TraceVariable (  const T &  obj  )  [inline]
 

Writes the current internal state of all members of the given object to the trace output. When the object contains pointer to types only the address is written. If the pointer values are also needed, successive calls of TraceVariable for the pointer members have to be done.
